6 An Act relating to public health; authorizing health
care providers to conduct pediatric screenings for
7 type 1 diabetes subject to parental consent;
providing for certain reimbursement; directing the
8 State Department of Health to seek certain funding;
directing promulgation of rules; providing for
9 codification; and providing an effective date.
10
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1-581 of Title 63, unless there
15 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16 A. Every health care provider in this state may conduct
17 pediatric screenings for type 1 diabetes in accordance with accepted
18 medical practices and subject to the informed consent of the child’s
19 parent or legal guardian.
20 B. The screenings described in subsection A of this section
21 shall be reimbursable under the state Medicaid program, subject to
22 receipt of any necessary federal approval and in accordance with
23 rules promulgated by the Oklahoma Health Care Authority Board.
24
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1427 Page 1

1 C. The State Department of Health shall seek grants and other
2 funding opportunities to support the provision of pediatric
3 screenings for type 1 diabetes as described in subsection A of this
4 section.
5 D. The Oklahoma Health Care Authority Board shall promulgate
6 rules necessary to implement subsection B of this section.
7 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
8 Passed the Senate the 25th day of March, 2026.
